data.description: Twilight Open House Friday, January 19th from 2-4pm!  Instant Equity, home appraised for over 700k!  * Seller Motivated * Welcome to single-level living at its finest, an entertainer's dream come true! This charming 4-bedroom, 2 bathroom home.   The interior of this home exudes warmth and character with hickory floors and cabinets throughout, not to mention a separate dry bar for your gathering. The heart of this home is the extra-large grand room, perfect for hosting family and friends, or simply relaxing in style.  Gas an electric options to stove and   This home is designed with accessibility in mind, featuring 32-inch doors and 36-inch hallways, making it easily navigable for individuals with mobility challenges.  Outside, on a generous 0.51-acre lot, you'll find a horse lover's paradise. This property is zoned for horses, giving you the opportunity to bring your equine companions. For those with an RV or other recreational vehicles, a 40-foot covered parking pad is ready to keep your vehicles protected from the elements.  But that's not all! The covered patio features hot and cold water, natural gas, and electricity. This space is ideal for hosting summer barbecues or enjoying the beautiful West Valley evenings.  For those who need a workspace, the property also includes a massive 40x20 metal shop with both 220 and 120 electric hookups. It's the perfect place to pursue your hobbies, projects, weld, or simply store your gear.  This delightful home is situated in a charming horse community right in the heart of West Valley. Here, you'll find a unique blend of rural living in the midst of the city. Picture yourself riding your horses along the streets or exploring the nearby Jordan River. It's a lifestyle that's truly one-of-a-kind.  Additionally, this property offers a fantastic financing opportunity. There's a VA assumable loan available with an incredibly low 2.25% interest rate on the remaining balance of $324,000 Don't miss the chance to make this extraordinary property your home sweet home.
